{"id":21754,"title":"Diffuse alopecia in an adolescent female: tinea capitis.","abstract":"\"Black dot\" tinea capitis is a common cause of alopecia in young patients. It is most commonly caused by a dermatophyte infection with Trichophyton tonsurans. This entity can be easily distinguished from alopecia areata with the use of hair/scalp dermoscopy. The use of oral terbinafine is effective in resolving the infection.","date":"2014-02-28","categories":"Bacterial Infections and Mycoses","split":"train","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/24588014","annotations":[{"name":"Tinea","weight":0.521091,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tinea"},{"name":"Infection","weight":0.280357,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Infection"},{"name":"Tinea capitis","weight":0.215812,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tinea_capitis"},{"name":"Dermatophyte","weight":0.203312,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dermatophyte"},{"name":"Trichophyton","weight":0.136645,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trichophyton"},{"name":"Terbinafine","weight":0.130256,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terbinafine"},{"name":"Trichophyton tonsurans","weight":0.0364124,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Trichophyton_tonsurans"},{"name":"Alopecia areata","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alopecia_areata"},{"name":"Dermatoscopy","weight":0.0297972,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dermatoscopy"},{"name":"Mouth","weight":0.0280659,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mouth"},{"name":"Adolescence","weight":0.0279596,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adolescence"},{"name":"Alopecia","weight":0.0274275,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alopecia"},{"name":"Entity","weight":0.0168623,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Entity"},{"name":"Race and ethnicity in the United States Census","weight":0.0168